name: DocumentEvent

properties.name: EVENT_ACTIVATED
properties.description: This event is fired after a document was activated.

properties.name: EVENT_BUSY
properties.description: This event is fired after the busy state of the document has changed.

properties.name: EVENT_CLOSED
properties.description: This event is fired when a document was closed.

properties.name: EVENT_DIRTY
properties.description: This event is fired after the dirty state of the document has changed.

properties.name: EVENT_EXPORTED
properties.description: This event is fired after a document was exported.

properties.name: EVENT_NEW
properties.description: This event is fired when a document was created or opened.

properties.name: EVENT_SAVED
properties.description: This event is fired after a document was saved.

properties.name: EVENT_TIMESELECTIONCHANGED
properties.description: This event is fired after the time selection of a document has changed.

properties.name: document
properties.description: Document object. With some events like e.g. DocumentEvent.Closed this property might be null.

description: This events is fired if one or more documents related event happened.
